  <CalDefinition Description="This calibration shall be used to set the initial default system language that is available in the SETTINGS SYSTEM LANGUAGE selection menu. The DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE shall be checked to confirm it is one of the available system languages enabled at a given time by the TARGET_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE_ENABLE_CALIBRATIONS. If at any time the value set for the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration is not one of the available system languages enabled by the TARGET_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE_ENABLE_CALIBRATIONS, the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration shall be set to a fail safe value based on the value the REGION calibration is set to at that time. For the purpose of referencing the REGION calibration to determine the fail safe value to set the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration if the REGION calibration is set to any of the following four REGION enumeration calibration values of 1.) EUROPE, 2.) AFRICA, 3.) AUSTRALIA, or 4.) INDIA, the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration shall be set to a fail safe default system language of ENGLISH_UK. Otherwise if the REGION calibration is not set to any one of these four Region enumeration calibration values, the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration shall be set to a fail safe default system language of ENGLISH_US." Name="DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE" References="GIS-507 and GIS-547" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_E4ARALEQEeO_VpIpRoy4MQ</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/24/2016</Date>
      <Description>Renamed this calibration from SYSTEM_LANGUAGE to DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE and updated the description of this calibration to clarify the intended purposes of this calibration. Also, updated the enumeration value names and values for each of the enumeration values for this calibration to correspond to the Software Mapping (Hexadecimal Converted) number shown in the GIS-547 to make it easier to follow corresponding enumeration references in relation to the GIS-547.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>6/13/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>4</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Enumeration>
      <EnumID>_sJrvYLEKEeO_VpIpRoy4MQ</EnumID>
      <Value>0</Value>
    </Enumeration>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="UNITED STATES IS DEFAULT COUNTRY CODE. Contry code will be based on RPO Calibration. As referenced in the GIS-331 Wifi Requirements Specification, this country code calibration is also being used for determining the regulatory wifi power variation settings to use for the wifi chip that shall be dynamically determined and set based on the value (country value) set for this calibration. Note, the value (country value) set for this calibration is determined by the country RPO (Regular Production Options Content) code for a given vehicle based on the PPC (Program Planning Content) for that vehicle, which represents the intended country of sell for that vehicle." Name="COUNTRY_CODE" References="GIS-331" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_J8iWULEaEeO_VpIpRoy4MQ</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>4</Version>
      <Date>6/24/2016</Date>
      <Description>Added on to the description shown for the COUNTRY_CODE calibration to clarify that this calibration is also being used as referenced in GIS-331 Wifi Calibration Specification for determining the regulatory wifi power variation settings to use for the wifi chip that shall be dynamically determined and set based on the value (country value) set for this calibration. Also, under the enumeration values for this calibration added additonal COUNTRY_CODE enumeration values that needed to be added. </Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>5</Version>
      <Date>6/13/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>6</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Enumeration>
      <EnumID>_NiUcILEYEeO_VpIpRoy4MQ</EnumID>
      <Value>49</Value>
    </Enumeration>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="LEFT HAND DRIVE IS DEFAULT. DRIVE_SIDE to comprehend vehicle configuration of Right Hand Drive (RHD) versus Left Hand Drive (LHD) with respect to GMLAN message location of driver front versus passenger front. Selection based on RPO Calibration." Name="DRIVER_SIDE" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
